A '''music jury''' is a final performance by a music student for a panel of jurors, usually consisting of faculty of the institution.  Students attend private lessons throughout the year, and they perform at the end of a semester or the year, to illustrate progress before the panel.<ref>{{cite news |title=What is a Music Jury? |author=Christopher Wilson |newspaper=The Easterner|date=April 3, 2002 |url=http://www.easterneronline.com/2.4790/what-is-a-music-jury-1.654298 |accessdate=May 13, 2010 }}</ref>  <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.juilliard.edu/college/calendar.html |title=The Juilliard School - College Division - Academic Calendar (2010-2011) |author= |date= |work= |publisher=[[The Juilliard School]] |accessdate=14 May 2010}}</ref>

